<task id="AIPU-023" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF StandaloneChatContextProvider + GET /api/ai/chat/context-mappings/standalone endpoint</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <wave>2</wave>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, api, backend, ai</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the BFF-side infrastructure for standalone (non-analysis) AI chat context resolution. The standalone chat context allows any Dataverse entity (matter, contact, account, opportunity, etc.) to be used as the context source for an AI chat session, not just analysis records.

    Deliverables:
    1. StandaloneChatContextProvider.cs — a service that resolves chat context mappings for standalone entity types. Mirrors AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs in structure.
    2. StandaloneChatContextEndpoints.cs — endpoint group registering GET /api/ai/chat/context-mappings/standalone with Redis caching, OBO auth filter, and proper ProblemDetails error handling.

    The endpoint accepts: entityType (string, required), entityId (Guid, required), tenantId (from claims, not query string).
    The endpoint returns: a ChatContextMapping object (list of available context fields and their display names for the given entity type).
    Cache key: chat-context:{tenantId}:standalone:{entityType}:{entityId}, TTL 30 minutes.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET 8 backend developer with expertise in Minimal API endpoint groups, Redis caching, and OBO authentication patterns</role>

  <goal>
    A working GET /api/ai/chat/context-mappings/standalone endpoint secured by OBO auth endpoint filter, cached in Redis with 30-minute TTL, and returning ChatContextMapping for any supported Dataverse entity type. Service and endpoint both compile and pass unit tests.
  </goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/StandaloneChatContextEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/StandaloneChatContextProvider.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/AiToolEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Auth/OboAuthEndpointFilter.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Caching/RedisCacheService.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No Azure Functions. This is a Minimal API endpoint group registered in Program.cs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Authorization via endpoint filter only — use OboAuthEndpointFilter (or equivalent). No global middleware for resource-level auth. tenantId extracted from authenticated claims, never from query string.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-009">Cache context mappings in Redis. Cache key pattern: chat-context:{tenantId}:standalone:{entityType}:{entityId}. TTL: 30 minutes. Use RedisCacheService (or IDistributedCache), not in-memory cache.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism: register StandaloneChatContextProvider as a concrete singleton (not behind an interface) unless a test seam is genuinely required. Total project DI registrations must stay at or below 15 non-framework services.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI endpoint follows existing AI tool endpoint patterns. No separate Azure service — extends BFF API.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Mirror AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs structure exactly: same constructor pattern, same return type (ChatContextMapping or equivalent), same error handling (throws domain exceptions caught by endpoint filter or exception handler).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">entityType must be validated against an allowlist of supported Dataverse entity logical names. Return 400 ProblemDetails for unsupported entity types.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">entityId in the query string must be validated as a valid Guid. Return 400 ProblemDetails on parse failure.</constraint>
  </constraints>

