  <steps>
    <step>Read src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs in full. Note constructor parameters, method signatures, return types, and exception handling patterns.</step>
    <step>Read src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/AiToolEndpoints.cs to understand endpoint group registration pattern, filter application, and ProblemDetails usage.</step>
    <step>Read src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Auth/OboAuthEndpointFilter.cs to understand filter interface and claims extraction.</step>
    <step>Read src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Caching/RedisCacheService.cs (or IDistributedCache usage) to understand cache get/set pattern and TTL configuration.</step>
    <step>Read src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs to identify where to register the new endpoint group and the DI registration location for StandaloneChatContextProvider.</step>
    <step>Create src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/StandaloneChatContextProvider.cs:
      - Constructor: inject ILogger&lt;StandaloneChatContextProvider&gt; and any Dataverse/Graph client needed for entity field discovery
      - Method: Task&lt;ChatContextMapping&gt; ResolveAsync(string entityType, Guid entityId, string tenantId, CancellationToken ct)
      - Implement allowlist of supported entity logical names (at minimum: contact, account, opportunity, incident, spaarke_matter)
      - Return 400-equivalent domain exception for unsupported entity types
      - Resolve context field mappings for the given entity type (field logical name → display label pairs).</step>
    <step>Create src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/StandaloneChatContextEndpoints.cs:
      - MapGroup("/api/ai/chat/context-mappings") with AddEndpointFilter&lt;OboAuthEndpointFilter&gt;()
      - GET /standalone: validate entityType (allowlist), validate entityId (Guid.TryParse), extract tenantId from claims
      - Check Redis cache with key chat-context:{tenantId}:standalone:{entityType}:{entityId}
      - On cache miss: call StandaloneChatContextProvider.ResolveAsync, cache result with 30-min TTL
      - Return 200 ChatContextMapping on success, 400 ProblemDetails on invalid input, 404 ProblemDetails if entity not found.</step>
    <step>Register in Program.cs: app.MapStandaloneChatContextEndpoints() (extension method) and services.AddSingleton&lt;StandaloneChatContextProvider&gt;().</step>
    <step>Run dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ to confirm zero compilation errors.</step>
    <step>Write a unit test in tests/ mirroring the AnalysisChatContextResolver test pattern: test cache hit path (returns cached result, no provider call), cache miss path (provider called, result cached), invalid entityType (returns 400), invalid entityId (returns 400).</step>
    <step>Run dotnet test to confirm tests pass.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>StandaloneChatContextProvider.cs exists with ResolveAsync method taking entityType, entityId, tenantId, and CancellationToken. Mirrors AnalysisChatContextResolver structure.</criterion>
    <criterion>GET /api/ai/chat/context-mappings/standalone endpoint is registered and secured with OboAuthEndpointFilter. tenantId is extracted from authenticated claims, never from the query string.</criterion>
    <criterion>Redis cache is checked before calling provider. Cache key follows pattern: chat-context:{tenantId}:standalone:{entityType}:{entityId}. Cache TTL is 30 minutes.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unsupported entityType values return 400 ProblemDetails with a descriptive error message.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unparseable entityId (not a valid Guid) returns 400 ProblemDetails.</criterion>
    <criterion>Entity not found returns 404 ProblemDetails.</criterion>
    <criterion>New service is registered in Program.cs DI. Total non-framework DI registrations remain at or below 15 (ADR-010).</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build passes with zero errors and zero warnings for the BFF project.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests cover: cache hit, cache miss + populate, invalid entityType, invalid entityId. All tests pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
